Based on a short story by H.P. Lovecraft, the undisputed master of the macabre, 
Dagon tells the story of Paul Marsh, a young man who discovers that the truth 
will not set him free instead it condemns him to a waking nightmare of 
unrelenting horror. A boating accident off the coast of Spain sends Paul and 
his girlfriend Barbara to the decrepit fishing village of Imboca looking for help. 
As night falls, people start to disappear and things not quite human start to 
appear. Paul finds himself pursued by the entire town. Running for his life, 
he uncovers Imboca&#039;s dark secret: that they pray to Dagon, a monstrous god of the 
sea. And Dagon&#039;s unholy offspring are freakish half-human 
creatures on the loose in Imboca...
